{|{{Infobox aircraft begin |name = XA-39 |image = |size = |alt = |caption = |long caption = }}{{Infobox aircraft type |type = Ground-attack aircraft |national origin = [[United States]] |manufacturer = |builder = [[Kaiser-Fleetwings]] |designer = |design group = |first flight = |introduced = |introdction = |retired = |status = |primary user = [[United States Army Air Forces]] |more users = |produced = |number built = 0 |program cost = |unit cost = |developed from = |variants with their own articles = |developed into = }} |} The '''Kaiser-Fleetwings A-39''' was a project by [[Kaiser-Fleetwings]] in the 1942–1943 period for an [[attack aircraft]] powered by a single [[Pratt & Whitney]] [[Pratt & Whitney R-2800|R-2800]] [[radial engine]]. It was to be armed with four .50 caliber [[machine gun]]s and two 37&nbsp;mm [[cannon]]s, along with up to {{convert|3000|lb}} of bombs.<ref name="AAA">{{cite book|last=Johnson|first=E.R.|title=American Attack Aircraft since 1926|year=2012|publisher=McFarland & Company|location=Jefferson, NC|isbn=978-0786471621|pages=419–420|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GmFhOCYckfQC&pg=PA419&lpg=PA419&dq=Kaiser-Fleetwings+A-39&source=bl&ots=y_6M8z2kJF&sig=t6xb6O8JtyJEfkP2P7zB5TwguZY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=jQRYUaewDoj8rAGB5oGQCA&ved=0CD4Q6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=Kaiser-Fleetwings%20A-39&f=false}}</ref> The A-39 was canceled before any prototypes were built.<ref name="AAA"/>
